<h2>The Chicago Plumbing Market</h2>
<p class="body-text">Chicago's aging housing stock — much of it built before 1960 — creates constant demand for plumbing services. From the bungalow belt on the Northwest Side to the vintage two-flats in Lincoln Park, Chicago homes require frequent plumbing repairs, repipes, and sewer line replacements. This means plumbing vans are parked in residential neighborhoods across the city every single day.</p>
<p class="body-text">The suburban market is equally competitive. Homeowners in <a href="/naperville/" style="color:var(--gold)">Naperville</a>, <a href="/schaumburg/" style="color:var(--gold)">Schaumburg</a>, <a href="/arlington-heights/" style="color:var(--gold)">Arlington Heights</a>, <a href="/elmhurst/" style="color:var(--gold)">Elmhurst</a>, and <a href="/oak-park/" style="color:var(--gold)">Oak Park</a> have dozens of plumbing companies to choose from. The companies with branded fleets win more calls because they're perceived as established, professional, and trustworthy — before the homeowner even picks up the phone.</p>
<p class="body-text">Chicago's climate adds urgency: frozen pipes in January, sump pump failures in April, and sewer backups during summer storms all drive emergency plumbing calls. When a homeowner's basement is flooding at midnight, they call the plumber whose van they've seen in their neighborhood — the one with the big phone number on the side.</p>
<h2>What Makes an Effective Plumbing Van Wrap?</h2>
<ul class="services">
<li><em>Oversized Phone Number</em> — The #1 element. Must be readable from 50+ feet away. This is what generates calls from neighborhoods.</li>
<li><strong>24/7 Emergency Service</strong> — If you offer emergency plumbing, make it the most prominent text on the van. Emergency callouts drive the highest-value jobs.</li>
<li><em>Service List</em> — "Drains · Water Heaters · Sewer · Remodel · Emergency" tells customers exactly what you do at a glance.</li>
<li><em>License Number</em> — Illinois requires displaying your plumbing license. A visible license number on your wrap builds instant trust.</li>
<li><strong>Clean Design</strong> — Avoid cluttered wraps. The best plumbing van wraps use bold colors, clear typography, and white space to ensure readability at speed.</li>
<li><em>Website &amp; Reviews</em> — Include your website URL and a review score ("4.9★ on Google") to drive online engagement.</li>
</ul>
